String multiline concatenation should be replaced with Text Blocks
In Java 15 Text Blocks are now official and can be used. The most common pattern for multiline strings in Java < 15 was to write String concatenation. Now itâ€™s possible to do it in a more natural way using Text Blocks. 
### Noncompliant
String textBlock =
               "<html>\n" +
               "    <body>\n" +
               "        <tag>\n" +
               "        </tag>\n" +
               "    </body>\n" +
               "</html>";
### Compliant
String textBlock = """
        <html>
            <body>
                <tag>
                </tag>
            </body>
        </html>""";
### Noncompliant
{{BUGGY}}
### Compliant
